======================================================================
DEEPER: I(3) mod 9, mod 27 STRUCTURE
======================================================================

n=7, 5000 samples:
  I(3) mod 9: {1: 1826, 4: 1790, 7: 1384}
  I(3) mod 27: {1: 633, 4: 479, 7: 544, 10: 633, 13: 695, 16: 482, 19: 560, 22: 616, 25: 358}
  α₁ mod 3: {0: 1826, 1: 1790, 2: 1384}

  Correspondence α₁ mod 3 → I(3) mod 9:
    α₁ ≡ 0 (mod 3) → I(3) mod 9 ∈ [1]
      actual=1, expected from (1+3·0) mod 9 = 1
    α₁ ≡ 1 (mod 3) → I(3) mod 9 ∈ [4]
      actual=4, expected from (1+3·1) mod 9 = 4
    α₁ ≡ 2 (mod 3) → I(3) mod 9 ∈ [7]
      actual=7, expected from (1+3·2) mod 9 = 7

======================================================================
THE VANDERMONDE EXTRACTION: α₁ FROM (H, I(3))
======================================================================

α₂ = (2·I(3) - 3·H + 1) / 6
α₁ = (H - 1 - 4·α₂) / 2

At n=7, this extracts α₁ = c3 + c5 + c7 (total odd cycles)
α₂ = total disjoint pairs of odd cycles

α₁ determines (c3,c5,c7) individually? 48 ambiguous / 62 total

(α₁,α₂) determines c3? Ambiguous: 21 / 164
(α₁,α₂) determines c5? Ambiguous: 23 / 164
(α₁,α₂) determines c7? Ambiguous: 30 / 164

